# {{PROJECT_NAME}} — Reuse Registry & Architecture

This rule enforces architectural constraints and dictates which org assets to reuse or exclude.

## Architectural Requirements
- **Agent Script Only**: Use the Agent Script `.agent` DSL for all agent configurations. DO NOT use legacy `genAiPlugin`, `genAiFunction`, or `genAiPlanner` metadata.
- **Integration policy**: {{LIVE_OR_MOCKED}} — e.g. "No live HTTP callouts; {{EXTERNAL_SYSTEM}} is mocked with Apex returning static data."
- **Flows over Apex**: Prefer Autolaunched Flows over Apex for simple SOQL queries. Use `@InvocableMethod` Apex only when Flows can't do it.
- **Lightning Types**: {{LIGHTNING_TYPE_NOTE}} — e.g. "`{{TYPE_NAME}}` requires Enhanced Chat v2; Classic Chat is NOT supported."

### EXCLUDE (SKIP)
Do NOT deploy or use:
- {{NAMED_CREDENTIALS_TO_SKIP}}
- {{LIVE_API_CLASSES_TO_SKIP}}
- Legacy Agentforce metadata (`genAiPlugins`, `genAiPlanners`, `genAiPlannerBundles`).

